20260719:
	* Release 1.9
	* Relicensed from GPL-2+ to GPL-3+, matching the GPLv3 text COPYING
	  has carried since 2012
	* Ported from SDL 1.x to SDL2; added a CMake build alongside autotools
	* https support via OpenSSL (optional, feature-detected in both build
	  systems): certificate verification against the system trust store,
	  -k/--insecure to accept bad certificates, TLS >= 1.2
	* IPv6 support (getaddrinfo, bracketed [::1]:port literals)
	* HTTP: proper HTTP/1.1 response framing, follow 3xx redirects (up to
	  5 hops), chunked transfer decoding, size and time limits
	* -K/--keep to retain downloaded files instead of deleting on exit
	* Dropped FTP (was advertised but never implemented)
	* Arbitrary pan and zoom (mouse drag/wheel + keyboard), unified on a
	  single GPU transform
	* On-screen filename display (n toggles, N cycles position), with an
	  embedded 8x8 font
	* -r now does a real fullscreen mode switch (closest available mode,
	  via SDL_SetWindowDisplayMode); the svgalib-era @depth suffix is gone
	* Handle oversized images (clamp window to display, downscale to fit)
	* Decoded-image cache; software-renderer fallback when no acceleration
	* Security hardening of the download path; async-signal-safe shutdown
	* GitHub Actions CI (Linux/macOS/FreeBSD) and a self-contained network
	  test suite
	* Pre-release audit fixes: skip HTTP 1xx interim responses, prompt
	  Ctrl+C during stalled transfers, redraw on window expose, honor -s
	  with a single image, refuse redirects to unsupported schemes

